== Properties ==

=== Algebraic properties of the formal power series ring ===
formula_23 is an associative algebra over formula_5 which contains the ring formula_24 of polynomials over formula_5; the polynomials correspond to the sequences which end in zeros.

The Jacobson radical of formula_23 is the ideal generated by formula_43 and the Jacobson radical of formula_5; this is implied by the element invertibility criterion discussed above.

The maximal ideals of formula_23 all arise from those in formula_5 in the following manner: an ideal formula_222 of formula_23 is maximal if and only if formula_224 is a maximal ideal of formula_5 and formula_222 is generated as an ideal by formula_43 and formula_224.

Several algebraic properties of formula_5 are inherited by formula_23:

* if formula_5 is a local ring, then so is formula_23 (with the set of non units the unique maximal ideal),
* if formula_5 is Noetherian, then so is formula_23 (a version of the Hilbert basis theorem),
* if formula_5 is an integral domain, then so is formula_23, and
* if formula_237 is a field, then formula_146 is a discrete valuation ring.

=== Topological properties of the formal power series ring ===
The metric space formula_239 is complete.

The ring formula_23 is compact if and only if &quot;R&quot; is finite. This follows from Tychonoff&#x27;s theorem and the characterisation of the topology on formula_23 as a product topology.

=== Weierstrass preparation ===

The ring of formal power series with coefficients in a complete local ring satisfies the Weierstrass preparation theorem.

==Applications==
Formal power series can be used to solve recurrences occurring in number theory and combinatorics. For an example involving finding a closed form expression for the Fibonacci numbers, see the article on Examples of generating functions.

One can use formal power series to prove several relations familiar from analysis in a purely algebraic setting. Consider for instance the following elements of formula_242:

:formula_243
:formula_244

Then one can show that

:formula_245
:formula_246
:formula_247

The last one being valid in the ring formula_248

For &quot;K&quot; a field, the ring formula_249 is often used as the &quot;standard, most general&quot; complete local ring over &quot;K&quot; in algebra.

==Interpreting formal power series as functions==

In mathematical analysis, every convergent power series defines a function with values in the real or complex numbers. Formal power series over certain special rings can also be interpreted as functions, but one has to be careful with the domain and codomain. Let

