:formula_261

and

:formula_262

Unlike in the case of bona fide functions, these formulas are not definitions but have to be proved.

Since the topology on formula_23 is the formula_264-adic topology and formula_23 is complete, we can in particular apply power series to other power series, provided that the arguments don&#x27;t have constant coefficients (so that they belong to the ideal formula_264): formula_267, formula_268 and formula_269 are all well defined for any formal power series formula_270

With this formalism, we can give an explicit formula for the multiplicative inverse of a power series formula_151 whose constant coefficient formula_272 is invertible in formula_5:

