==Generalizations==

=== Formal Laurent series ===
The formal Laurent series over a ring formula_5 are defined in a similar way to a formal power series, except that we also allow finitely many terms of negative degree. That is, they are the series that can be written as

:formula_282

for some integer formula_283, so that there are only finitely many negative formula_18 with formula_285. (This is different from the classical Laurent series of complex analysis.) For a non-zero formal Laurent series, the minimal integer formula_18 such that formula_287 is called the &quot;order&quot; of formula_151 and is denoted formula_289 (The order ord(0) of the zero series is formula_290.)

Multiplication of such series can be defined. Indeed, similarly to the definition for formal power series, the coefficient of formula_291 of two series with respective sequences of coefficients formula_292 and formula_293 is
formula_294
This sum has only finitely many nonzero terms because of the assumed vanishing of coefficients at sufficiently negative indices.

The formal Laurent series form the ring of formal Laurent series over formula_5, denoted by formula_296. It is equal to the localization of the ring formula_23 of formal power series with respect to the set of positive powers of formula_43. If formula_144 is a field, then formula_300 is in fact a field, which may alternatively be obtained as the field of fractions of the integral domain formula_146.

As with formula_23, the ring formula_296 of formal Laurent series may be endowed with the structure of a topological ring by introducing the metric
formula_304
(In particular, formula_305 implies that formula_306

One may define formal differentiation for formal Laurent series in the natural (term-by-term) way. Precisely, the formal derivative of the formal Laurent series formula_151 above is
formula_308
which is again a formal Laurent series. If formula_151 is a non-constant formal Laurent series and with coefficients in a field of characteristic 0, then one has
formula_310
However, in general this is not the case since the factor formula_18 for the lowest order term could be equal to 0 in formula_5.

